goals.question: What is the distribution of component sizes?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the range of sizes of the software components and identify any outliers.

goals.question: What is the average size of the software components?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of average size of components by parent
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the parent components with the largest and smallest average sizes of software components.

goals.question: What is the relationship between component size and parent component?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of size vs parent
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify any patterns or trends in the relationship between the size of software components and their parent components.

goals.question: What are the most common software components?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of top 10 most common components
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the most frequently occurring software components in the dataset.

goals.question: What is the distribution of parent components?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the distribution of parent components and identify any outliers or patterns.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='size', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['size'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['size'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of component sizes?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby('parent')['size'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='parent', y='size', data=data_grouped)
    plt.title('What is the average size of the software components?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Parent Component ID')
    plt.ylabel('Average Size (bytes)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    chart = sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='parent', y='size')
    plt.title("What is the relationship between component size and parent component?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Parent Component ID")
    plt.ylabel("Component Size (bytes)")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    top_components = data['name'].value_counts().head(10)
    sns.barplot(x=top_components.index, y=top_components.values)
    plt.title('What are the most common software components?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Software Components')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(top_components.index, title='Components', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
